# Frontend rules

## Stack

- Next.js app router
- TypeScript
- React components
- Plain CSS unless a styling system is intentionally added later

## UI style

- Low-fi DOS terminal
- Monospace text
- High contrast
- Chunky panels
- Clear destructive states
- Accessible buttons and labels

## Component principles

- Keep components small.
- Put shared types in `src/lib/types.ts`.
- Put reusable copy builders in `src/lib`.
- Avoid mixing API calls into presentation components.
- Make destructive state transitions explicit.

## Accessibility

- All interactive controls need labels or visible text.
- Do not rely only on color for destructive state.
- Support keyboard navigation.
- Do not use animations that block comprehension.
